Connecticut Energy Corp saidits Southern Connecticut Gas Co unit filed with stateregulators a letter of intent to raise its rates by 2.7 pct, orabout 4.2 mln dlrs, beginning in late 1987.    The company said it expects to file a formal applicationwith the Connecticut Department of Public Utility Controlwithin 60 days.    The company said a rate increase is needed to cover higheroperating and maintenance expenses that have occurred since itlast received a rate hike of three pct, or 4.8 mln dlrs, inJanuary 1985. Reuter&#3;